  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Justice for Female Survivors of Sexual Violence in Colombia</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Sisma Mujer will be legally representing women who have survived sexual violence in five strategically chosen cases, with the aim of bringing them justice. If successful, this litigation work could create favourable jurisprudence that will help address the general problem of impunity, which could go on to help other women in similar circumstances. The project will identify existing barriers women&#x2019;s face when seeking justice, recommendations of how to address those in different contexts and what litigation strategies should be applied.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">&#xF0B4;Legal representation and support accompaniment for five cases of sexual violence.  
&#xF0B4;Counselling and psychosocial support to all six female victims. 
&#xF0B4;Psychosocial support - depending on the case, there could also be other aspects of the victim&#x2019;s life that have been affected, for example, health issues, job situation, housing, social relationships, stigma, family and economic security. 
&#xF0B4;Production of a technical report which will identify the barriers faced by women when accessing justice. 
&#xF0B4;Drafting the protocol, &#x2018;for crimes against sexual freedom and integrity&#x2019; to the General Prosecutor.
&#xF0B4;Two technical cases presented to CEDAW (Committee on the Elimination of Discrimination against Women) and the Inter-American Human Rights Commission on sexual based violence.  
&#xF0B4;Publish articles, blogs, press releases and interviews to generate public interest in Colombia and the UK on issues related to sexual and gender based violence.</narrative>
  </description>
